About 80 people have been arrested at Lebombo for trying to get into the country illegally. And, Beitbridge seems ghostly this afternoon, compared with the chaos a few weeks ago. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - About 80 people have been arrested at the Lebombo border post for trying to get into South Africa illegally. On Monday, the South African government announced the closure of 20 land borders in a bid to slow the spread of COVID-19. Border queues are considered superspreader events. Watch the video above for more details on this story